# HTTPS Protocol Fundamentals

This section documents the completion of a short course on the **HTTPS protocol** and secure web communications.

Although the course content is no longer available in the learning dashboard, the certification confirms the successful completion of the program.

---

# Topics Covered

The course introduced the fundamentals of secure web communication, including:

* HTTP vs HTTPS
* TLS/SSL encryption
* Digital certificates
* Certificate Authorities (CA)
* Public Key Infrastructure (PKI)
* Secure communication between clients and servers
* Importance of HTTPS in modern web security

---

# Key Concepts Learned

## HTTPS

HTTPS (HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure) is the secure version of HTTP. It encrypts communication between a client and a server using **TLS (Transport Layer Security)**.

## TLS Encryption

TLS provides:

* Data confidentiality
* Data integrity
* Authentication of the server

## Digital Certificates

Web servers use digital certificates issued by trusted Certificate Authorities to prove their identity.

